{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-tsx","path":"/texts/tipitaka/sutta-pitaka/samyutta-nikaya/SN2/subrahma-sutta/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Standing to one side, the god Subrahmā addressed the Buddha in verse:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>“This mind is always anxious, <br>\nthis mind is always stressed <br>\nabout stresses that haven’t arisen <br>\nand those that have. <br>\nIf there is a state free of anxiety, <br>\nplease answer my question.” <br>\n<br>\n“Not without understanding and austerity, <br>\nnot without restraining the sense faculties, <br>\nnot without letting go of everything, <br>\ndo I see safety for living creatures.”</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>That is what the Buddha said. … The god vanished right there.</p>\n<div style=\"text-align:center\">\n<p><a href=\"/texts/tipitaka/sutta-pitaka/samyutta-nikaya/SN2/kakudha-sutta/\">SN.2.18. Kakudha Sutta (“With Kakudha”)</a></p>\n</div>","htmlAst":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Standing to one side, the god Subrahmā addressed the Buddha in verse:"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"blockquote","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"“This mind is always anxious, "},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nthis mind is always stressed "},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nabout stresses that haven’t arisen "},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nand those that have. "},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nIf there is a state free of anxiety, "},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nplease answer my question.” "},{"type":"